22/05/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- At a cabinet meeting Wednesday (May 21st), Prime Minister Sali Berisha announced that beginning in July salaries and pensions will be increased to help offset overall price hikes.
He also lashed out at the media for questioning whether the government has the will and the power to help the public handle the higher prices.
At the meeting, the government also decided to pay the rents of those displaced by the March 15th explosions at the Gerdec ammunition depot.
(BalkanWeb, Alsat, Telegrafi - 21/05/08)
